<!-- ── About + signup ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="h-bottom">
	<div class="h-about">
		<p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">What is this</p>
		<h2 class="display h-about-h2">Built for<br>the obsessed.</h2>
		<p class="h-about-body">Backyard ultra is unlike anything else in endurance sport. One 4.167-mile loop, every hour on the hour, until only one runner crosses the start line and nobody else does. Also called a last-one-standing backyard ultra marathon, the format creates a specific kind of athlete: patient, stubborn, calculating. A race experience that standard results pages don't capture.</p>
		<p class="h-about-body">BACKYARDS pulls live data from raceresult.com and turns it into something you can actually read. Lap pacing trends, DNF distribution, multi-race comparisons. For spectators tracking a friend across 72 hours. For athletes studying the field. For anyone who's looked at a backyard ultra results page and wanted more.</p>
		<a href="/pace-tool/" class="h-about-link">Compare splits across races →</a>
		<a href="/learn/what-is-backyard-ultra/" class="h-about-link" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">New to the format? Start here →</a>
	</div>

